<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Everton have now officially confirmed the signing of James Rodriguez, with the Colombian star become Carlo Ancelotti's marquee signing of the summer.</p>

<p>Toffees boss Ancelotti has finally pulled off the coup, knowing James well from his time in charge at Real Madrid.</p>

<p>The 29-year-old is understood to have cost Everton in the region of £20million, and has now finally brought his torrid time at Real Madrid to an end.</p>

<p>Everton have announced the signing of James Rodriguez by using a mocked up graphic</p>

<p>The Colombian has finally brought his Real Madrid nightmare to an end and moved to England </p>

<p>Everton thrilled their fanbase on Monday evening by teasing the arrival, before publishing a video in which James could be heard saying: 'I'm here, I'm happy, I'm proud to be a Blue.' </p>

<p>The Toffees then reeled off all of the 29-year-old's honours during his career so far, along with the teams he has played for, before showing a mocked up graphic of James in the Everton shirt.</p>
